  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "The average cost per couple to travel to Bhutan from Ahmedabad can vary widely depending on several factors. Here's a breakdown of the expenses and estimated costs:\n\n**Factors Influencing the Cost:**\n\n*   **Duration of Trip:** A longer trip will naturally cost more. Common trips are 7-10 days.\n*   **Time of Year:** Peak season (spring and autumn) will be more expensive due to higher demand for flights and accommodation. Shoulder seasons (early spring, late autumn) offer a balance of good weather and lower prices. Winter and summer are the least expensive, but the weather might be a concern.\n*   **Accommodation:** You can choose from budget guesthouses, mid-range hotels, or luxury resorts. Prices vary significantly.\n*   **Transportation within Bhutan:**  The cost of a private car and driver versus joining group tours makes a difference.\n*   **Activities:** Entrance fees to monasteries, trekking permits, and special cultural performances all add to the cost.\n*   **Shopping:** Souvenirs and handicrafts can contribute to your overall expenses.\n*   **Agency Fees:** If booking through a tour operator (which is required for independent travel to Bhutan), their commission will be factored into the price.\n*   **Flight Costs:** Airfare from Ahmedabad to Paro (Bhutan's only international airport) will vary depending on the airline, time of booking, and season.\n\n**Mandatory Costs:**\n\n*   **Sustainable Development Fee (SDF):** This is a per-person, per-night fee levied by the Bhutanese government. As of 2024, the SDF for tourists is **USD 100 per person, per night**.\n\n**Estimated Cost Breakdown (per couple):**\n\n**Budget Trip (7 Days/6 Nights):**\n\n*   **Flights (Ahmedabad to Paro roundtrip):** INR 70,000 - 100,000 (This can vary greatly)\n*   **SDF (USD 100 per person per night = USD 1200):** INR 100,000 (approximate conversion)\n*   **Accommodation (budget guesthouses):** INR 15,000 - 25,000\n*   **Food:** INR 15,000 - 20,000\n*   **Transportation (private car with driver, shared with other travelers if possible):** INR 25,000 - 35,000\n*   **Visa Fee:** INR 8000 (USD 40 Per Person)\n*   **Miscellaneous (entrance fees, tips, etc.):** INR 10,000 - 15,000\n*   **Travel Insurance:** INR 3,000 - 5,000\n\n**Total (Budget): INR 245,000 - 308,000 (approximately) or USD 2900-3600**\n\n**Mid-Range Trip (7 Days/6 Nights):**\n\n*   **Flights (Ahmedabad to Paro roundtrip):** INR 70,000 - 100,000\n*   **SDF:** INR 100,000\n*   **Accommodation (3-star hotels):** INR 35,000 - 50,000\n*   **Food:** INR 25,000 - 35,000\n*   **Transportation (private car with driver):** INR 40,000 - 60,000\n*   **Visa Fee:** INR 8000\n*   **Miscellaneous:** INR 20,000 - 30,000\n*   **Travel Insurance:** INR 3,000 - 5,000\n\n**Total (Mid-Range): INR 301,000 - 388,000 (approximately) or USD 3600-4600**\n\n**Luxury Trip (7 Days/6 Nights):**\n\n*   **Flights (Ahmedabad to Paro roundtrip):** INR 70,000 - 100,000\n*   **SDF:** INR 100,000\n*   **Accommodation (luxury resorts):** INR 100,000 - 200,000+\n*   **Food:** INR 50,000 - 80,000\n*   **Transportation (premium private car with driver):** INR 60,000 - 80,000\n*   **Visa Fee:** INR 8000\n*   **Miscellaneous (private guides, special activities):** INR 50,000 - 100,000\n*   **Travel Insurance:** INR 3,000 - 5,000\n\n**Total (Luxury): INR 441,000 - 673,000+ (approximately) or USD 5300-8000+**\n\n**Important Considerations and Tips:**\n\n*   **Book Flights in Advance:**  Book your flights as early as possible to get the best deals.\n*   **Travel Agency:**  Choose a reputable travel agency that specializes in Bhutan.  They can handle your visa, accommodation, transportation, and itinerary.  Get quotes from multiple agencies to compare prices.  Ensure the agency is registered with the Tourism Council of Bhutan (TCB).\n*   **Negotiate:**  While bargaining isn't a common practice in Bhutan, you can sometimes negotiate prices for souvenirs or handicrafts.\n*   **Travel Insurance:**  Get comprehensive travel insurance that covers medical emergencies, trip cancellations, and lost luggage.\n*   **Currency:**  The Bhutanese currency is the Ngultrum (BTN). It is pegged to the Indian Rupee (INR) at par. Indian Rupees are widely accepted in Bhutan, but higher denominations (INR 500 and INR 2000) may not be.\n*   **Sustainable Tourism:**  Be mindful of the environment and local culture.  Choose eco-friendly accommodations and respect Bhutanese traditions.\n*   **Flexibility:**  Be prepared for unexpected delays or changes in your itinerary.  Bhutan is a mountainous country, and weather conditions can sometimes disrupt travel plans.\n\n**Therefore, to answer your question directly, the average cost per couple to travel to Bhutan from Ahmedabad for a 7-day trip can range from approximately INR 245,000 to INR 673,000 or USD 2900 to USD 8000+ depending on your travel style and choices.** It is always better to get a customized quote from a registered Bhutanese tour operator to get the most accurate price for your specific requirements.\n\n**Disclaimer:** Prices are estimates and can vary significantly. The SDF is the biggest controllable factor, as it's fixed.  Your choice of accommodation, transportation, and activities will primarily affect the rest of the budget. This information is for general guidance only. Please contact a travel agent for an accurate quote.\n",
